.SH NAME
drm_fb_helper_set_suspend \- wrapper around fb_set_suspend
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" drm_fb_helper_set_suspend
.BI "(struct drm_fb_helper *fb_helper "  ","
.BI "bool suspend "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "fb_helper" 12
driver-allocated fbdev helper, can be NULL
.IP "suspend" 12
whether to suspend or resume
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
A wrapper around fb_set_suspend implemented by fbdev core.
Use \fBdrm_fb_helper_set_suspend_unlocked\fP if you don't need to take
the lock yourself
